#: ../../source/help/getting-started/creating-teams.rst:2
msgid "Creating Teams"
msgstr "Creare Team"

#: ../../source/help/getting-started/creating-teams.rst:4
msgid ""
"A team is a digital workspace where you and your teammates can "
"collaborate in Mattermost. Depending on how Mattermost is set up in your "
"organization, you can belong to one team or multiple teams."
msgstr ""
"Un Team è uno spazio di lavoro digitale in cui tu e i componenti del tuo team potete "
"collaborare in Mattermost. A seconda delle impostazioni di Mattermost nella tua organizzazione, "
"puoi appartenere a un solo team o a più team."

#: ../../source/help/getting-started/creating-teams.rst:6
msgid ""
"New teams can be created if the System Admin has **Enable Team Creation**"
" set to true in the System Console."
msgstr ""
"Nuovi team possono essere creati se l'amministratore di sistema ha impostato a true l'opzione "
"**Enable Team Creation** nella Console di Sistema."

#: ../../source/help/getting-started/creating-teams.rst:9
msgid "Methods to Create a Team"
msgstr "Metodi per Creare un Team"

#: ../../source/help/getting-started/creating-teams.rst:11
msgid ""
"If team creation is enabled by the System Admin, teams can be created "
"from the team sidebar or Main Menu. The person who creates a team will "
"automatically be assigned the Team Admin role for that team."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/help/getting-started/creating-teams.rst:14
msgid "Team Sidebar"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/help/getting-started/creating-teams.rst:15
msgid ""
"If you belong to more than one team, a team sidebar will appear left of "
"your channel list on the left-hand sidebar."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/help/getting-started/creating-teams.rst:19
msgid ""
"Click the \"+\" icon at the bottom of the team sidebar, then click "
"**Create a New Team** on the team selection page, which guides you "
"through the rest of the setup steps. If this option is not visible on the"
" web page, then the System Admin has disabled team creation."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/help/getting-started/creating-teams.rst:21
msgid ""
"If you have no other teams to join, clicking the \"+\" icon brings you "
"directly to the team creation page if team creation is enabled."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/help/getting-started/creating-teams.rst:24
msgid "Main Menu"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/help/getting-started/creating-teams.rst:25
msgid ""
"From your current Mattermost team, click on the **Main Menu** > **Create "
"a New Team**. If this option is not visible in the menu, then the System "
"Admin has disabled team creation."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/help/getting-started/creating-teams.rst:28
msgid "Team Name and URL Selection"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/help/getting-started/creating-teams.rst:30
msgid ""
"There are a few details and restrictions to consider when selecting a "
"team name and team URL."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/help/getting-started/creating-teams.rst:33
msgid "Team Name"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/help/getting-started/creating-teams.rst:35
msgid "This is the display name of your team that appears in menus and headings."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/help/getting-started/creating-teams.rst:37
msgid "It can contain any letters, numbers or symbols."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/help/getting-started/creating-teams.rst:38
msgid "It is case sensitive."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/help/getting-started/creating-teams.rst:39
#: ../../source/help/getting-started/creating-teams.rst:49
msgid "It must be 2–15 characters in length."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/help/getting-started/creating-teams.rst:42
msgid "Team URL"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/help/getting-started/creating-teams.rst:44
msgid ""
"The team URL is part of the web address that navigates to your team on "
"the system domain, ``https://domain.com/teamurl/``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/help/getting-started/creating-teams.rst:47
msgid "It may contain only lowercase letters, numbers and dashes."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/help/getting-started/creating-teams.rst:48
msgid "It must start with a letter and cannot end in a dash."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/help/getting-started/creating-teams.rst:50
msgid ""
"It cannot start with the following restricted words: ``signup``, "
"``login``, ``admin``, ``channel``, ``post``, ``api``, ``oauth``, "
"``error``, ``help``, ``plugins``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/help/getting-started/creating-teams.rst:55
msgid "Best Practices for Using a Single Team vs. Multiple Teams"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/help/getting-started/creating-teams.rst:57
msgid "Mattermost can be deployed both to a single team and to multiple teams."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/help/getting-started/creating-teams.rst:59
msgid ""
"Currently, we recommend deploying to a single team for the following "
"reasons:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/help/getting-started/creating-teams.rst:61
msgid ""
"Single team deployments promote communication across the organization. "
"When you add multiple teams, groups can become isolated."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/help/getting-started/creating-teams.rst:62
msgid ""
"We don’t yet support search or channels across teams, which can impact "
"the cross-team user experience. This includes general searches, flagged "
"posts and recent mentions."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/help/getting-started/creating-teams.rst:63
msgid ""
"Integrations (e.g., webhooks and slash commands) are only persistent "
"across single team deployments."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/help/getting-started/creating-teams.rst:65
msgid ""
"However, some Mattermost customers prefer multiple team deployments for "
"the following reasons:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/help/getting-started/creating-teams.rst:67
msgid ""
"Teams are useful when there is a purpose for each of them. For example, "
"one team is used for staff members and another team for external users."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/help/getting-started/creating-teams.rst:68
msgid ""
"Performance is better when users are scattered across multiple teams "
"instead of all in the same one. With multiple teams, there is less "
"content to load per team or channel switch and database queries are "
"faster."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/help/getting-started/creating-teams.rst:69
msgid ""
"Creating a shared team for all users, and using `advanced permissions "
"<https://docs.mattermost.com/deployment/advanced-"
"permissions.html#recipes>`__ to control who can create channels and add "
"members to the shared team, improves cross-team collaboration when using "
"multiple teams. Additionally, an `annoucement banner "
"<https://docs.mattermost.com/administration/announcement-banner.html>`__ "
"can be used to provide system wide announcements."
msgstr ""

